There is some recent work that builds further on Lambek's pregroups
and crucially relies on the categorical structure to assign meaning
to sentences:

A Compositional Distributional Model of Meaning
Stephen Clark, Bob Coecke, Mehrnoosh Sadrzadeh
http://www.pps.jussieu.fr/~mehrs/AAAI_2008.pdf

Bell States and Negative Sentences in the Distributed Model of Meaning
Anne Preller, Mehrnoosh Sadrzadeh
http://hal-lirmm.ccsd.cnrs.fr/docs/00/37/50/37/PDF/QPL09.pdf

Lambek himself had in the past emphasized similarities between sentence
structure and the uses of monoidal categories in physics, ...

